# 7. Check Whether All Elements Are Unique

## Problem

Check whether every element appears only once.

### Example

```python
numbers = (1, 2, 3, 4)
```

## Built-in Solution

```python
numbers = (1, 2, 3, 4)

if len(numbers) == len(set(numbers)):
    print("Unique")
else:
    print("Not Unique")
```

## Pure Logic Solution

```python
numbers = (1, 2, 3, 4)

unique = True

for i in range(len(numbers)):

    for j in range(i + 1, len(numbers)):

        if numbers[i] == numbers[j]:
            unique = False
            break

if unique:
    print("Unique")
else:
    print("Not Unique")
```

### Output

```text
Unique
```

